##############################################################
#
#  Setup
#
#

Context("Numeric");
#given
$d = random(18,22,1);
$t1 = random(60,80,2);
$t2 = 20;
$t3 = 30;

#image scale
$imgScale = .2;

#image aspect ratio
$width = $imgScale*2075;
$height = $imgScale*1168;

#computation 
$tbc = $t1;
$tcd = $t1-$t2;
$tda = $t1-$t2+$t3;
$g = 210/(2*(1+.3));
$j = pi/2 * ($d**4)/16;
$phi = ($tbc*.8 + $tcd*.6 + $tda*.2)/($g*$j)*1000*180/pi;

#set tolerance
Context()->flags->set(
tolerance=>.05);

##############################################################
#
#  PGML 
#
#

BEGIN_PGML

[@ image("UBC-SM-18-069.png", width=>[$width], height=>[$height]) @]*

As shown in the diagram, a steel shaft with a [`[$d]`] [`mm`] diameter supports the three external torques, [`T_B=[$t1]`] [`Nm`], [`T_C=[$t2]`] [`Nm`], and [`T_D=[$t3]`] [`Nm`]. What is the angle of twist at [`B`], the end of the rod? For steel, use parameters [`E = 210`] [`GPa`], [`\nu = 0.3`].

[`\phi=`] [____]{"$phi"}[`^{\circ}`]  

END_PGML

